<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-02-14T07:41:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-02-14T07:41:00-05:00" n="901" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d901">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 855.48/457</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in the Netherlands</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_LM1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Langhorne</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">The Hague</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-02-14T13:00:00+00:19">
                                    <hi rend="italic">February 14, 1917, 1 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                                <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 2 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>716. <persName corresp="#p_WB1">Whitlock</persName> sends following
                            message by courier:</p>
                        <p>Negotiations regarding the relief, the status of Commission for Relief in
                            Belgium, and my position are proceeding. I hope to send a report by next
                            courier. Will the Department in the meantime take no final action in
                            regard to <persName>Herter</persName>’s telegram sent from Berne?</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_LM1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Langhorne</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>